Recursion :    functional calling itself untill the condition met.

example;     printing the name N times

          printName(String name, int count, int N) {

            if ( count == N ){
                return                --->>  This is base case,  once this pass the  recursion will end.
                      }
            System.out.println(name);

            printName(name,count + 1, N);

           }


Example 2 :         Print the number from 1 to N                      1 to 3   , step 1 : printnum(1,3) > base condn fails > print 1 > printnum(1+1,3) 

                   void  PrintNum ( int current, int N ){                        step 2 :  Printnum(2,3) > base Fails > print 2 > Printnum( 2+1,3)

                     if( current > N){                                           step 3:  Printnum(3,3) > base fails > print 3 > printnum(3+1, 3)
                              return; }
                                                                                step 4: Printnum(4,3) > base pass > return
                    System.out.println(current);

                    PrintNum ( current + 1, N);
                                                                      TC : O(N)   >> uses the N operations
                    }
                                                                      SC : O(N)   >> store in N stacks
